         <abstract>
            <p>A sequence of interpolation series is given which generalizes Whittaker's cardinal function to the case of Hermite interpolation. By integrating the interpolation series, a sequence of new quadrature formulae for $\int^\infty_{-\infty} f(x) dx$ is obtained. Derivative-free remainders are stated for these interpolation and quadrature formulae.</p>
          </abstract>
